==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interosculate
<hw>In`ter*os"cu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To kiss together to touch. See
<er>Osculate</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>To have the character of, or to
lie between, two distinct groups.</def></p>

<p><ent>Interosseous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Interosseal</ent>⟦br⟧
